trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of application-specific <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"></xref> instances used in combination with <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en samling av programspesifikk <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"> </xref> forekomster brukes sammen med <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The PackageStore defines a reference collections of package that are open and active in the application.
trans-unit.target: PackageStore definerer en referanse samlinger av pakken er åpen og aktive i applikasjonen.

trans-unit.source: Packages added to the PackageStore are accessed is by their key URI value.
trans-unit.target: Pakker som er lagt til i PackageStore er tilgang av deres nøkkelverdien URI.

trans-unit.source: The PackageStore supports three common uses: 1.
trans-unit.target: PackageStore støtter tre vanlige bruker: 1.

trans-unit.source: Accessing <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> data through <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.
trans-unit.target: Tilgang til <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>data via <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>

trans-unit.source: The application obtaining an instance of a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package> given the package's URI.
trans-unit.target: Programmet henting av en forekomst av en <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>angitt i pakken URI.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>

trans-unit.source: Accessing packages that are created and stored in a <xref:System.IO.MemoryStream>.
trans-unit.target: Tilgang til pakker som er opprettet og lagret i en <xref:System.IO.MemoryStream>.</xref:System.IO.MemoryStream>

trans-unit.source: To improve performance and minimize the overhead of repeated file open/close operations, the PackageStore is used to manage instances of packages accessed by <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> and directly by the application.
trans-unit.target: For å forbedre ytelse og begrense overhead gjentatte filen åpne/Lukk operasjoner, er PackageStore Hvis du vil administrere forekomster av pakker åpnes av <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>og direkte av programmet.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>

trans-unit.source: When accessing data in a package, the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package> address of a requested <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> is first checked to see if the package is already defined and open in the PackageStore.
trans-unit.target: Ved tilgang til data i en pakke av <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>adressen til en forespurte <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>kontrolleres først for å se om pakken er allerede definert og åpen i PackageStore.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>

trans-unit.source: If the package is defined as open in the PackageStore, requested parts can be accessed directly without repeatedly opening and closing the package for each request.
trans-unit.target: Hvis pakken er definert som åpen i PackageStore, kan få tilgang til forespurte deler direkte uten gjentatte ganger åpner og lukker pakken for hver forespørsel.

trans-unit.source: If your application opens a package with <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Open%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> can be called to add the package to the PackageStore.
trans-unit.target: Hvis programmet åpner en pakke med <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Open%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A>kan kalles for å legge til pakken i PackageStore.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Open%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A> should later be called to remove the package from the PackageStore prior to calling <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Close%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A>senere må kalles for å fjerne pakken fra PackageStore før du kaller <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Close%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Close%2A?displayProperty=fullName></xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A>

trans-unit.source: XPS packages opened with an <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A> constructor are automatically added and removed from the PackageStore when the document is created and disposed.
trans-unit.target: XPS pakker åpnes med en <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A>konstruktøren automatisk legges til og fjernes fra PackageStore når dokumentet er opprettet og fjernet.</xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A>

trans-unit.source: (You do not need to call <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> or <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A> separately for XPS packages opened with <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A> constructors.) The file I/O permissions of a package accessed through the PackageStore remains the same as the I/O permissions set on the package when it is opened.
trans-unit.target: (Du trenger ikke å kalle <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A>eller <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A>separat for XPS pakker åpnes med <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A>konstruktører.)</xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> Filen i/u-tillatelsene for en pakke tilgjengelig via PackageStore uendret som i/u-tillatelser som er angitt i pakken når den er åpnet.

trans-unit.source: The PackageStore only provides references to the packages that have been added the store.
trans-unit.target: PackageStore gir bare referanser til pakker som har blitt lagt til butikken.

trans-unit.source: It is up to the application to correctly open, update, and close each package.
trans-unit.target: Det er opp programmet på riktig måte å åpne, oppdatere og lukk hver pakke.

trans-unit.source: Packages added to the PackageStore can be accessed in multithreaded environments when they are used in combination with a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] parser such as <xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Pakker som er lagt til i PackageStore kan åpnes i miljøer med flere tråder når de brukes sammen med en [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] parseren som <xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: When operating in a multithreaded environment, the application must lock the package before access.
trans-unit.target: Når opererer i et flertrådsmiljø, må programmet låse pakken før tilgang.

trans-unit.source: Adds a <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"></xref> to the store.
trans-unit.target: Legger til en <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"> </xref> til butikken.

trans-unit.source: `packageUri` defines the package's key URI that is compared when you call <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.
trans-unit.target: `packageUri`definerer pakkens nøkkelen URI sammenlignes når du kaller <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>

trans-unit.source: If the `packageUri` matches the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> for a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> in a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> call, the package defined in the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore> is used to access the requested part.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den `packageUri` samsvarer med den <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>for en <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>i <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>samtalen, pakken er definert i <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore>brukes til å få tilgang til for forespurte.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the `packageUri` does not match the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> for a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> in a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> call, the package with the specified URI is opened to access the requested part.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den `packageUri` samsvarer ikke med den <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>for en <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>i en <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>Oppkalling pakke med den angitte URIEN er åpnet for å få tilgang for forespurte.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>
